 Frankfurt School. Subtly and persuasively argued, his book will become an indispensable reference point for all concerned with twentieth-century German history and thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts and societyxHistoryx20th centuryxGermany. 0aArts and societyzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnlightenmentxGermany. 0aEnlightenmentzGermanyxIntellectual life. 0aEnlightenmentzGermany. 0aJewsxIntellectual lifexGermany. 0aJewszGermanyxIntellectual life. 0aJewszGermany. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aadorno.  aanti semitism.  aanti war.  abenjamin.  abloch.  acritical theory.  acritique of the german intelligentsia.  adadaism.  adialectic of enlightenment.  aeurope.  afrankfurt school.  agerman history.  agerman philosophy.  aheidegger.  ahistory.  ahorkheimer.  ahugo ball.  ainterwar period.  ajasper.  ajewish intellectuals.  ajewish messianism.  aletter on humanism.  amessiah.  amessianic.  anationalism.  anonfiction.  aphilosophy.  aquestion of german guilt.  asocial theory.  aworld war one.  aworld war two.  aww1.  aww2.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052022690640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520926257?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520926257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520926257/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles